gw.testharness

Annotation Type Upgrade


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Inherited
 @UseHandlerFactory(value=ProductExtendableTagHandlerFactory.class)
public @interface Upgrade
    Annotation to denote that a test will restore a backed up database (usually against a previous release) and therefore will have to upgrade that database before proceeding. @Archive tests will work, but only the primary archive will be restored.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String releaseName
      The release we're upgrading from.
      int releaseVersion
      The number of the release we're upgrading from.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String backupName 
      boolean runConsistencyCheckAfterUpgrade 

    • Element Detail

      • releaseName

        public abstract java.lang.String releaseName
        The release we're upgrading from.
        Returns:
        e.g. "bedrock" (lowercase)

      • releaseVersion

        public abstract int releaseVersion
        The number of the release we're upgrading from.
        Returns:
        e.g. 505

      • backupName

        public abstract java.lang.String backupName
        Returns:
        Given name of the backup. This is not the file name. By default, this is the same as the test name.
        Default:
        ""

      • runConsistencyCheckAfterUpgrade

        public abstract boolean runConsistencyCheckAfterUpgrade
        Returns:
        Whether to run consistency check after upgrade
        Default:
        true
